oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Winn and McCraw
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of Winn and McCraw, a sale stable, located at Third Street and Main Street in Clarksville, Tennessee. Men are standing in the street with horses. W. A. McCraw, an owner, is sitting in a horse-drawn buggy. The horse's name was "Lady."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Stables; Horses; Carriages & coaches
